(18270, 1, '2020-06-23 14:49:24', '2020-06-23 11:49:24', '<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>TERMS &amp; CONDITIONS</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The following terms and conditions apply to all website development / design services provided by Don M. Ouwens (\'me\' or \'I\') to the. A \'project\' is any work undertaken or service provided by me for the Client on their request and as described in the proposal document or any written communication to that Client.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>ACCEPTANCE</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is not necessary for any Client to have signed an acceptance of these terms and conditions for them to apply. If a Client accepts a quote then the Client will be deemed to have satisfied themselves as to the terms applying and have accepted these terms and conditions in full. Please read these terms and conditions carefully. Any purchase or use of our services implies that you have read and accepted our terms and conditions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>LEGALITIES, COPYRIGHT AND INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I cannot be held responsible for anything adversely affecting the Client\'s business operation, sales, or profitability that might be claimed is a result of a service offered. I will not be liable for costs incurred, compensation or loss of earnings due to the failure to meet agreed deadlines. This includes the situation in which the Client has been late in supplying materials, or has not approved or signed off work on time, at any stage.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Please ensure that any images or content supplied is legally available for you to use. I cannot be held responsible for the illegal use of images, content or format of material supplied by the Client.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Where images used for any project of the Client have been purchased by me on behalf of the Client, these images are restricted by license for the use within the organisation of the Client only and are limited to 15 images per project. I am not liable for misuse of these images by the Client or any other person\'s copying, altering or distributing the images to individuals or other organisations.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>PAY TERMS</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Charges for services to be provided by me are defined in the project quotation that the Client receives via e-mail or printed. Quotations are valid for a period of 30 days. I reserve the right to alter or decline to provide a quotation after expiry of the 30 days.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Unless agreed otherwise with the Client, all services require an advance payment of a minimum of fifty (50) percent of the project quotation total before the work is supplied to the Client for review. The remaining fifty (50) percent of the project quotation total due upon completion of the work, prior to upload to the server or release of materials.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Payment for services is due by bank transfer. All invoices should be paid in full within seven (7) days after sending the invoice. Invoices that remain unpaid seven (7) days after the date of the invoice will be assessed a service charge in the amount of the higher of one and one-half percent (1.5%) or 30 per month of the total amount due. Bank details will be made available on invoices and can be found at the bottom of this page.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Client agrees to reimburse me for any additional expenses necessary for the completion of the work. Examples would be purchase of special fonts, stock photography etc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I own all sketches,